An Asian immigrant arrested in the Kariobangi slum has been charged with being in the country illegally.Trivedi Shirshir, according to court documents, is an Indian citizen and does not have a visa. In another count, Shirshir was accused of forging a passport on March 30.He is accused of presenting the passport to an officer, claiming it was issued by the Director of Immigration.Police were on patrol when they ran into Shirshir and asked him for his documents. He presented the passport, but could not explain where he got it from.Shirshir was taken to the police station and the passport forwarded to the Department of Immigration before appearing in court. He denied the charge before chief magistrate Emilly Ominde and was released on Sh200,000 bond with a surety of a similar amount. The case will be heard on July 26.